<br>
Sar had a stalker that is now aggravating the shit out of Kerridwynn.  She told similar stories.  I'll have to ask Kerri what char she's playing now. Anyway,I digress. The sheer amount of mental instability on the net(in any &quot;chat type&quot; venue) is sort of scary to me. <p><center><img src="http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/traesig.jpg"><br><i>Still keeping things sane(or not) at <a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner" target="_new">Sar's Corner.</a><br>Yes, you can touch my <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=588147" target="_new">clothes.</a></i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syrienne>Syrienne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Misery</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stalking on EQ</span><hr size=1> Like I said.. I cannot say what went on in the other guild other than what I have gotten from the freaks contacting me constantly... but I can say what I have had to deal with.<br>
<br>
Achsia came to our guild and did not mention one word about her previous one... she joined to be with her RL boyfriend... then these tells started.<br>
