&lt;shakes her head&gt; Freaks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dessirra>dessirra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/20/03 12:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stalking on EQ</span><hr size=1> I think most of the females on Eq have had to deal with harassment and/or stalking, my own character included.  I also know of several females who play male characters simply to get away from this type of behaviour.  My character likes to flirt.  This is harmless fun and most of the males on the server I believe know this and enjoy flirting back.  Unfortunately the few who can not seperate RP flirting from RL flirting are the ones who cause the problems.  I suspect they are also this way in RL which is kind of scary.  <br>
